# .env — Development Environment Variables
#
# These values are injected into the app at build time by Vite.
# In the code, read them with: import.meta.env.VITE_VARIABLE_NAME
#
# IMPORTANT: Only variables prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the browser.
# Never put secrets (passwords, private keys) in here — this file gets
# bundled into the JavaScript that anyone can read in their browser.
#
# For production (on AWS), set these as real environment variables
# on the server or in your CI/CD pipeline — not in this file.

# API base URL — all axios requests are prefixed with this.
# "/api" works in development because vite.config.ts has a proxy:
#   /api/admin/leads → http://localhost:3000/admin/leads (strips /api)
# In production, change this to your real backend domain:
#   VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com
VITE_API_URL=/api
